args.command:
cat << 'EOF' > nyt_news.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The New York Times - Today's Hot News (March 5, 2026)</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --nyt-black: #000;
            --nyt-gray: #666;
            --nyt-border: #dfdfdf;
            --nyt-bg: #fff;
            --nyt-accent: #326891;
            --font-serif: "Cheltenham", "Georgia", serif;
            --font-sans: "Franklin Gothic", "Helvetica", sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            font-family: var(--font-serif);
            background-color: var(--nyt-bg);
            color: var(--nyt-black);
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
        }

        header {
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 4px double var(--nyt-black);
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 3.5rem;
            margin: 0;
            letter-spacing: -1px;
        }

        .date-bar {
            border-top: 1px solid var(--nyt-black);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nyt-black);
            padding: 5px 0;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-family: var(--font-sans);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        main {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 1000px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 40px;
        }

        section {
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nyt-border);
            padding-bottom: 20px;
        }

        section h2 {
            font-family: var(--font-sans);
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--nyt-accent);
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--nyt-accent);
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .article {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .article h3 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin: 0 0 10px 0;
            line-height: 1.2;
        }

        .article p {
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .footer {
            margin-top: 50px;
            font-family: var(--font-sans);
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--nyt-gray);
            text-align: center;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--nyt-border);
            padding-top: 20px;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 1000px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; }
            main { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>The New York Times</h1>
    <div class="date-bar">Thursday, March 5, 2026</div>
</header>

<main>
    <section>
        <h2>World</h2>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Iran War Escalation: School Strike in Minab</h3>
            <p>A devastating strike on a school in southern Iran has reportedly killed at least 175 people, including many schoolgirls. The facility was located near an IRGC naval base.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Secret Outreach to U.S. Intelligence</h3>
            <p>Iranian intelligence operatives have reportedly made indirect contact with the CIA to explore potential de-escalation talks, though U.S. officials remain skeptical.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Politics</h2>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Senate Faces War Powers Vote</h3>
            <p>Congress remains deeply divided as the Senate prepares for a critical vote on war powers amid the ongoing conflict with Iran.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>U.S. Operations in Ecuador</h3>
            <p>The Trump administration has launched joint military operations with Ecuadorian forces to combat "narco-terrorist" groups in South America.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>James Talarico Wins Texas Democratic Primary</h3>
            <p>In one of the most expensive primaries in history, James Talarico has emerged victorious in the Texas Senate race.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Business & Markets</h2>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Markets Edge Higher on Peace Hopes</h3>
            <p>The S&P 500 showed gains following reports of potential diplomatic outreach from Iran and assurances of oil market stability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Oil Prices Stabilize</h3>
            <p>U.S. oil benchmarks trade around $75 per barrel as the Navy begins escorting tankers through the Strait of Hormuz.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Games & Culture</h2>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Connections #998</h3>
            <p>Today's categories include "Bits of Hardware" and "Places Where Ideas are Developed."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="article">
            <h3>Wordle & Mini Crossword</h3>
            <p>Millions continue their daily ritual with today's puzzles, featuring clues like "Poli ___" and "Person with a superior attitude."</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<div class="footer">
    &copy; 2026 The New York Times Company. Generated by Gemini CLI for personal use.
</div>

</body>
</html>
EOF
